Head : 1.3–1.4× as wide as high; vertex 2.8–3.5× as wide as eye, antennal segment II 0.5–0.7× as long as basal width of pronotum, 0.5–0.9× as long as width of head. Thorax : Pronotum 2.1–2.6× as wide as long and 0.9– 1.3× as wide as head; length of hemelytra ranging from reaching anterior margin of abdominal tergum VI to covering abdominal tergum IX, typically hemelytra reaching abdominal segment VII; clavus and cuneus not delimited; claval commissure somewhat shorter or as long as inner claval margin; posterior and lateral margins rounded and posterior margin truncate. GENITALIA: Sclerotized rings of dorsal labiate plate oval, medial sclerites short, blade-shaped, straight and not twisted (fig. 16); posterior wall of bursa copulatrix with trapeziform sclerite membranous medially and sclerotized at sides, incision on the anterior margin broad and not reaching middle of sclerite, anterior angles of this sclerite not dentate, posterior margin without sclerites only with membrane somewhat dentate (fig. 19); vulva with straight sclerites not forming a circle (as in fig. 19,
